A Master player of any champion does that, not just Aatrox Masters. 
A Master will most likely dominate their rivals in lane unless they play against others Masters.

And if you are so mad about {{champion:266}} 
then play {{champion:24}} {{champion:240}} {{champion:92}} {{champion:114}} {{champion:58}}  and there you go, Aatrox now has zero presence in the game.

Edit 1: And before you say that Kled doesn't beat Aatrox early game, learn to play Kled. I just watched 2 diamonds Aatrox vs Kled and Kled completely destroyed him early game, mid game, and late game because the player knew how to play kled and didn't just walk into Aatrox's face.

Edit 2: 

{{champion:240}} has a 55.98% WR against {{champion:266}}
{{champion:114}} has a 56.76% WR against {{champion:266}}
{{champion:58}} has a 55.57% WR against {{champion:266}} 
{{champion:24}} has a 56.14% WR against {{champion:266}}
{{champion:157}} has a 57.43% WR against {{champion:266}} 
{{champion:92}} has a 58.90% WR against {{champion:266}}
{{champion:82}} has a 59.10% WR against {{champion:266}}.

There is no excuse for being unable to beat Aatrox with these champions. I know people sometimes want to put all the blame on the enemy champion to feel better but this is reality. Most people that know how to play these champions will destroy Aatrox.
